's western-formed mindset the book detects the influence of his printing enterprise upon the transition from scribal tradition to print culture.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aPrintingzTurkeyxHistory. 0aPublishers and publishingzTurkeyxHistory. 70(DE-601)1044440960(DE-588)4008598-3aBuchdruck2gnd 70(DE-601)1046655480(DE-588)4013134-8aDruckwerk2gnd 70(DE-601)1056434080(DE-588)4138343-6aVerleger2gnd 70(DE-601)1057449050(DE-588)4124801-6aDrucktechnik2gnd 70(DE-601)10612949X0(DE-588)4063004-3aVerlag2gnd 7aHISTORY / Middle East / Turkey & Ottoman Empire.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2018z978311068818440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618116192423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618116192.jpg  a978-3-11-068818-4  ASP eBook Package 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG